  "texts": [
    "Portfolio weight limits can also be used to avoid excessive concentration of a portfolio, or limit short positions.",
    "For example, w max = 0.15 means that our portfolio cannot hold more than 15% of the total portfolio value in any one asset.",
    "(Here we adopt the convention that in a vector-scalar inequality, the scalar is implicitly multiplied by 1.)",
    "As another example, w min = -0.05 means that the short position in any asset can never exceed 5% of the total portfolio value.",
    "For large portfolios it is reasonable to also limit holdings relative to the asset capitalization, e.g., to require that our portfolio holdings of each asset are no more than 10% of the asset capitalization."
  ],
